Theme: US-Israel-Iran Conflict

Israel and the US launched Operation 'Roar of the Lion' and 'Epic Fury', combining kinetic strikes with a massive cyberattack that caused a 96% drop in Iran's internet connectivity.

Tags: Iran, Cyber Warfare, Internet Blackout, Geopolitics

objects.name: Malicious QuickLens Chrome Extension
objects.description:
The QuickLens extension was compromised to deploy ClickFix attacks and steal crypto-wallet seed phrases from thousands of users.

Analysis:
A supply chain attack on a legitimate browser extension that leverages social engineering (fake Google Update prompts) to execute malicious code locally and drain crypto assets.

Recommendations:
- Remove QuickLens extension immediately and scan for local malware.
- Reset all browser-stored passwords and transfer funds to a new crypto wallet.

objects.name: Agent Tesla via Phishing & Process Hollowing
objects.description:
A new phishing campaign delivering Agent Tesla credential stealer through business-themed emails using layered scripts that stay in memory.

Analysis:
Memory-only execution tactics used to bypass traditional disk-based antivirus scans.

Recommendations:
- Enable MFA for all business email accounts.
- Deploy endpoint detection (EDR) capable of monitoring memory process hollowing.

objects.content: The period ending March 1, 2026, is marked by a massive convergence of kinetic and cyber warfare, specifically with the launch of Operation 'Epic Fury' and 'Roar of the Lion' by US and Israeli forces against Iran, resulting in a near-total (96%) internet blackout in the country. This state-level activity is mirrored by high-impact criminal operations, including the exposure of 38 million accounts in the Canadian Tire breach and the 'ClawJacked' vulnerability targeting the burgeoning AI agent ecosystem (OpenClaw). The discovery of a critical 'one-packet-to-root' flaw in Juniper PTX routers (CVE-2026-21902) and widespread reconnaissance against SonicWall infrastructure by ransomware groups like Akira signify an imminent threat to global network backbones and critical infrastructure.
